**Abstract:**
Working notes titled "Finding my way. Essay One." Discusses evidentialism vs. affectivism, intellectualism vs. voluntarism in medieval theology. References Aquinas vs. Kilwardby ("chef de l'Augustinisme philosophique") and contrasts primacy of intellect-truth-vision versus primacy of love-will-practical adhesion. Notes on Kantian division between speculative and practical reason, arguing Kant is an evidentialist who implicitly attributes primacy to vision.

